Buyers: All auction animals will be housed at the Adams County Fairgrounds. They are available for viewing on Saturday 8am - 11 am. Please practice social distancing if you choose to come see them. We look forward to a busy sale day and hope to see you there!

post_text: The Warden School District would like to welcome Mr. Chris Lupo as our new High School Principal. Mr. Lupo recently moved back to Moses Lake from the Duvall area where he was a principal for the Riverview School District. Chris was a teacher in the Warden Elementary School for a number of years, early in his teaching career, and remembers having several of our current staff when they were in elementary school! Welcome back to Warden, Mr Lupo!

post_text:
At the end of July, 2020 the Warden School District (WSD) Technology Department will begin overhauling all of the WSD websites beginning with Elementary, Middle, and High Schools. During the overhaul, the sites will be inaccessible and service of the sites is not expected to resume until mid September. The main WSD site will remain in operation to continue to provide information and services. Updates regarding the schools will be made available on the District website, as well as some updates for the community will be made here, on the WSD Facebook page.

We look forward to presenting contemporary websites that are more feature rich and streamlined to navigate in hopes of better serving the Warden Community and stakeholders. Thank you for your patience and understanding while we are hard at work on the websites and preparing for the coming school year. Stay safe, stay healthy, and Go Cougs! Warden School District Technology Department

post_text:
Seniors,
Here are some final details and reminders about graduation:

• Decorate your vehicle before arriving at the Annex for the parade (social distancing guidelines apply)
• Wear your cap gown, stole and tassel
• Make sure family vehicle (not graduate vehicle) has parking pass or they will not be allowed admittance to the ceremony
• Only normal passenger vehicles (cars, pickups suvs vans). No buses, trailers, or farm equipment
• Remember everyone must stay in their vehicles except the graduate when they are receiving their diploma
• There will not be restroom facilities available on campus
• Livestream will be available on the District and High School webpages for community and family who are unable to attend
• This information will also be available in student email

We look forward to celebrating with you!!

The Warden School District would like to make available the results of our 2020-12 Planning Survey. We had 176 responses to the survey from parents, students, staff and community members. The survey results document is 25 pages in length and may take a moment to download.

We have edited any personal identifiable information from the written comments. The first pages are the graphed results of the multiple choice questions. Following are the pages with written comments for questions #8, 17 & 18, and the last pages are the written comments for the "Other" response to multiple questions.

The administration wants to thank everyone who responded to the survey, we appreciate the input and will be using this information to guide us for our reopening planning this fall.

https://drive.google.com/file/d/1moHAcIAzOvP3KENLfrc9M_rMZ7ZbyqMq/view?usp=sharing

post_text:
WSD 2020-21 FALL PLANNING SURVEY
Today, June 18 is officially the last day of school of the 2019-20 school year for the Warden School District. We thank the students, parents and community for working with us as we were challenged during these unprecedented times. We appreciate our staff who accepted a number of different assignments and tasks as we transitioned to extended and then remote learning. We are planning for the beginning of the next school year in the fall and realize there are a number areas we will be working to improve.

We have prepared a survey we are asking parents, students, staff and community to respond to. For staff and community we have six questions to answer to help us plan for the fall. For parents and students we have an additional 11 questions concerning your experience with remote learning this spring.

The survey will be open until June 30. Please click this link to access the survey. https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=PlZWoY3-tEiySowT1jWwQ3euqc-Nig5Ipa_b2aGsHEFURVdJSjEwUks5WDgzMUVDR1BEWE85OUFNRC4u

post_text:
Good morning, Warden! The end of the academic year is fast approaching and the last meal distribution for the year will be tomorrow, Wednesday, June 17th.

The Washington State Department of Social & Health Services and the Washington Office of Superintendent of Public Instruction have collaborated together to provide some relief during the summer for Washington families with children in grades K-12 that qualify for free and reduced-priced meals. Families may apply for Pandemic EBT benefits at k12.wa.us/PEBT.

Obtenga ayuda para comprar alimentos mientras las escuelas están cerradas.

Si su hijo/a está en los grados K-12 y califica para comidas gratis o de precio reducido, o si asiste a una escuela donde las comidas son gratuitas para todos los estudiantes, puede solicitar los beneficios de EBT pandémica.

Aprende más en k12.wa.us/PEBT

Exciting news Warden! Friday, 5/15 marks the last Technology Checkout for the year from 11:30am to 12:30pm, which means 3rd and 4th grades are getting their turn! Anyone who had previously signed up for laptops or laptops and hotspots are welcome to come tomorrow too!

A quick word on internet hotspots, the WSD Technology Department has taken additional precautions to keep students safe. However, it requires hands on with both the hotspots and laptops that will not be reasonable to do on the spot tomorrow. If you are checking out BOTH a laptop and a hotspot tomorrow, then good news, the additional work has already been done. For those of you that already checked out laptop and reserved a hotspot or visa-versa, the WSD Technology Department will be opening a new phone line and will be posting hours to provide tech support for just this sort of thing. Details regarding the phone line and appointments will follow shortly.

post_text:
WMS Yearbooks, Memories of 2019-2020

The Warden Middle School Yearbook will be packed with photos and memories of the 2019-2020 school year.

You will not want to miss out on your copy. It covers activities from robotics to drama, plus dances and assemblies. The band and choir are well represented, and so are the fall and winter sports teams.

The 64-page book is something to keep forever — fun photo memories of a school year that didn’t quite work out as expected!

There will be pages allocated for your classmates to sign their names and write messages — when we are back together.

Yearbooks are currently for sale until July 1 for $30, at: http://jostensyearbooks.com/?REF=A09113610

#BeTheLightWA

This Friday, April 17 in honor of all Warden High School seniors in the class of 2020, Warden School District will join with other schools around the state of Washington and turn on the WHS Stadium Lights at 8:20 pm (20:20 military time). If you choose to view this celebration of our seniors, PLEASE continue to practice social distancing guidelines and remain in vehicles at all times while viewing this event.

Warden School District Community,

The Washington Interscholastic Activities Association (WIAA) published on 4/6/2020 that "The WIAA has received clarification that the order issued by Governor Inslee on Monday includes the cancellation of all in-person extracurricular athletics and activities through the end of the school year. This will include all regular season contests and practices as well as all postseason tournaments and championship events." Their complete update can be found at this link - http://wiaa.com/news.aspx?ID=681&Mon=3&Yr=2020

We have updated the Question and Answer document on the district webpage with recent questions and responses. The District admin team is participating in frequent meetings, webinars and discussions this week to piece together the next steps as we plan for school closure through the remainder of the school year. We will keep you updated on those plans and decisions. Thank you for your patience as we all navigate through these uncharted waters. Stay healthy.

Warden Athletics information:

This afternoon Governor Inslee issued a state-wide requirement for all public schools to close beginning next Tuesday, March 17 through April 24. During this time period, all Warden School District athletic contests and practices have been cancelled. While school is closed, district athletic facilities will also be closed to all community youth athletics and other outside organizations.

Athletic Directors and school administrators will be working together to determine what will happen with athletics when school re-opens. More information will be given when it becomes available.

post_text:
Parents and Guardians,
Governor Jay Inslee has ordered all public and private K-12 schools in the state of Washington to close for students from March 17 until at least April 24. The Warden School District is preparing and implementing plans to support the Governor’s directive. School will be open for students on Monday, March 16. The evening of Monday, March 16 at 7:00 pm in the high school gymnasium, the Warden School Board will be having a community meeting for parents to ask questions concerning the school closure and its impact to our community. The meeting will be limited to 250 attendees, if you plan to attend please only have one representative from your family. The school district will continue to make additional information available through the website and social media. Thank you.
text:
Parents and Guardians,
Governor Jay Inslee has ordered all public and private K-12 schools in the state of Washington to close for students from March 17 until at least April 24. The Warden School District is preparing and implementing plans to support the Governor’s directive. School will be open for students on Monday, March 16. The evening of Monday, March 16 at 7:00 pm in the high school gymnasium, the Warden School Board will be having a community meeting for parents to ask questions concerning the school closure and its impact to our community. The meeting will be limited to 250 attendees, if you plan to attend please only have one representative from your family. The school district will continue to make additional information available through the website and social media. Thank you.

Congratulations to our Warden Zero Robotics Team: Hunter, Derek, Omar, Kaitlyn, Magaly, Peyton and Jannet for earning 1st place in the Washington State Regional Competition and 1st in Washington State overall.

The Warden Zero Robotics Team spent three weeks working on a computer code to retrieve a satellite that lost its boosters while experimenting with ways to collect the space debris orbiting the earth. The Warden Zero Robotics Team worked directly with M.I.T. to create the master code for Washington State. The results of the collaborative efforts were sent to the International Space Station for a simulation contest against other participating states for the final competition, currently pending score review for National placement.

Way to go Warden Zero Robotics Team - your ability to overcome obstacles, along with your dedication and skill execution rocks. Good luck with this next stage of your learning and competition!

post_text:
Announcement:

The Warden School District is experiencing a devastating loss with the recent death of one of our Principals, Chris McKnight. Chris was in a fatal car accident yesterday, March 22nd around 4:00 pm on Highway 17. Chris served our district as a principal for eight (8) years and touched numerous lives. He served Warden as a Middle School Principal, Elementary Principal, and currently our 6th – 12th grade Co-Principal. The District and community are in the midst of establishing response and support plans to care for individuals that this event will impact.

The community is holding a candle light vigil tonight at 7:00, March 23rd at the District’s flagpole in memory and to honor the life and service Chris provided us all. All are invited to attend.

Chris was a dear friend, colleague, leader, and public servant. Our hearts and prayers go out to the entire McKnight family, friends, and the thousands of lives Chris devoted service to.

He will be deeply missed.

Sincerely,

Dr. David B. LaBounty
Superintendent
